T1  - Exact moments of the sample autocorrelations from series generated by general arima processes of order (p, d, q), d=0 or 1
AU  - De Gooijer, Jan G.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 14
IS  - 3
SP  - 365
EP  - 379
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/12/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(80)90033-0
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407680900330
AB  - Formulae for the numerical computation of the first four exact moments of the sample autocorrelations, given a time series realisation from a general autoregressive moving average process of order (p, d, q) with d=0 or 1, are presented. The exact mean and variance of the sample autocorrelations are computed for various sample sizes and several time series models. The evaluated results are compared with those obtained from approximate formulae for the mean and variance of the sample autocorrelations. A specification of the numerical accuracy of the first two exact moments is included.
